fields.name: John de Lancie
fields.star_info_1: John de Lancie is among SciFi fans probably best known for his portrayal of the iconic, enigmatic and all-powerful mischief maker in chief, Q. Star Trek fans around the world are eagerly awaiting de Lancie reprising his role of Q in the upcoming second season of Star Trek: Picard!
fields.star_info_2: De Lancie's other SciFi related roles include appearances in The Six Million Dollar Man, Batlestar Galactica, The New Twilight Zone, Stargate SG-1 and Torchwood. He also worked on several video games as an voice actor.

fields.name: John Barrowman
fields.star_info_1: John Barrowman can do it all! He is an actor, author, presenter, singer, and comic book writer. At conventions he is a force of nature. His most prominent SciFi roles include Captain Jack Harckness in Doctor Who and also Torchwood, and Malcolm Merlyn in the Arrowverse.
fields.star_info_2: Barrowman's other roles include appearances in Zero Dark Thirty, Desperate Housewives, Anything Goes, Evita, Chicage, La Cage aux Folles, and several concert performances. He also recorded several studio and compilation albums.

fields.name: Jason Isaacs
fields.star_info_1: SciFi fans know Jason Isaacs for his portrayal of Captain Gabriel Lorca in Star Trek: Discovery, Commander/Admiral Zhao in Avatar: The Last Airbender, Ronald Quincy in Armageddon, and his voice acting for Star Wars: Rebels. We will be sure to ask him whether there are any news about a new Star Trek series featuring Prime Lorca!
fields.star_info_2: Isaac's other roles include appearances in Black Hawk Down, The Tuxedo, Sex education, and of course, his portrayal of Lucius Malfoy in the Harry Potter movies. He currently stars as Dr. Rob Griffith in Good Sam and has completed several movies and series that are currently in post-production.

fields.name: Anthony Rapp
fields.star_info_1: Anthony Rapp currently plays the first openly gay character in Star Trek, Lieutenant Paul Stamets in Star Trek: Discovery. His other SciFi related roles include a guest appearance in The X-Files. He also worked on the video game Star Trek Online: Awakening as a voice actor and enjoys playing video games himself.
fields.star_info_2: Rapp is also a singer and started his career portraying Mark Cohen in the Broadway production of Rent, and later in the show's film version and tour. Other roles include appearances in Six Degrees of Separation, A Beautiful Mind, Kidnapped, and 13 Reasons Why.

fields.name: Wilson Cruz
fields.star_info_1: Wilson Cruz portrays Dr. Hugh Culber in Star Trek: Discovery and his character is in love with Anthony Rapp's Paul Stamet. Both actors are gay themselves and also friends. They will held a paid guest talk (free for package holders) together and we are happy to announce that all revenues from this talk will be donated to local LGBTQ-related projects!
fields.star_info_2: Cruz' other roles include Angel in the Broadway tour production of Rent, Gabriel in The People I've Slept With, Victor in Party of Five, and Dennis Vasquez in 13 Reasons Why

fields.name: Krysten Ritter
fields.star_info_1: Krysten Ritter is another multitalent. She is an actress, director, musician, author, and model. SciFi fans know her for  her portrayal of superhero Jessica Jones in Jessica Jones and The Defenders. She directed an episode in the third season of Jessica Jones.
fields.star_info_2: Ritter has also appeared in Gilmore Girls, Breaking Bad, The Blacklist, and El Camino: A Breaking Bad Movie.

fields.name: Seth MacFarlane
fields.star_info_1: Seth MacFarlane is an actor, animator, screenwriter, producer, film director, comedian, and singer! In 2017 he created the SciFi TV series The Orville. He is also a co-producer, and stars in the role of Captain Ed Mercer. MacFarlane also co-produced the series Cosmos: A Spacetime Odyseey hosted by Neil deGrasse Tyson.
fields.star_info_2: MacFarlane also created the TV series Family Guy and co-created American Dad. He wrote, directed, and starred in Ted, Ted 2, and A Million Ways to Die in the West. He has released six studio albums.

fields.name: Scott Grimes
fields.star_info_1: Scott Grimes is known among SciFi fans for his portrayal of Bradley Brown in Critters and Critters 2: The Main Course, guest appearances in The Twilight Zone, Star Trek: The Next Generation, and his current portrayal of Lieutenant Gordon Malloy in The Orville.
fields.star_info_2: Grimes' has also appeared in Crimson Tide, Robin Hood, 21 Jump Street, ER, Dexter, NCIS, Suits, Criminal Minds, NCIS: Los Angeles, and Justified.

fields.name: Elizabeth Olsen
fields.star_info_1: Elizabeth Olsen is famous among SciFi fans for her portrayal of Wanda Maximoff/Scarlet Witch in Captain America: The Winter Soldier, Captain America: Civil War, Avengers: Infinity War, Avengers: Endgame, and WandaVision. We can't wait to see her reprise the role in Doctor Strange in the Multiverse of Madness!
fields.star_info_2: Olsen also starred in Godzilla, Ingrid Goes West, Kodachrome, and Sorry for Your Loss, which she also executive produced.

fields.name: Summer Glau
fields.star_info_1: Summer Glau is well known among SciFi fans for her portrayals of River Tam in Firefly and Serenity, Tess Doerner in The 4400, and Cameron in Terminator: The Sarah Connor Chronicles. She also had a cameo in The Big Bang Theory.
fields.star_info_2: Glau also had roles in Angel, The Unit, Alphas, Hawai Five-0, Arrow, and Castle.

fields.name: Dominique Tipper
fields.star_info_1: Dominique Tipper is an actress, dancer, and singer-songwriter. She had her international breaktrough with her portrayal of Naomi Nagata in The Expanse and The Expanse: One Ship. She also played Maddie in MindGamers and worked as voice actress on video games.
fields.star_info_2: Tipper also had roles in Fast Girls, Vampire Academy, Fantastic Beasts and Where to Find Them, and Monday.

fields.name: Joseph Gordon-Levitt
fields.star_info_1: Joseph Gordon-Levitt is an actor and filmmaker. His SciFi related roles include Quantum Leap, G.I. Joe: The Rise of Cobra, Inception (those sharp suits!), and The Dark Knight Rises.
fields.star_info_2: Gordon-Levitt has received Golden Globe Awards for Best Actor - Motion Picture Musical or Comedy for his performances in 500 Days of Summer and 50/50. His other roles include Joe in Looper, Jon 'Jon Don' Martello Jr. in Don Jon, which he also directed and wrote, Edward Snowden in Snowden, and Josh Corman in Mr. Corman, which he directed, wrote and executive produced.
